{
  "info": {
    "name": "EV Charging Station Management System (CSMS)",
    "description": "Complete Postman collection for the Tucker Motors CSMS backend.\n\nRun requests in order:\n1. Boot Notification (registers the station)\n2. Start Transaction (returns a transactionId — copy it into the collection variable)\n3. Meter Values\n4. Stop Transaction\n5. Query APIs",
    "_postman_id": "csms-tucker-motors-v1",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl",       "value": "http://localhost:8080",  "type": "string" },
    { "key": "stationId",     "value": "EVSE-001",               "type": "string" },
    { "key": "transactionId", "value": "",                        "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-filled after running Start Transaction" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "OCPP Messages",
      "description": "Simulated OCPP 1.6 messages from a charging station to the CSMS",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Boot Notification",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Response status is Accepted', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('Accepted');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('currentTime is present', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().currentTime).to.be.a('string');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/ocpp/boot-notification", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","ocpp","boot-notification"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"stationId\": \"{{stationId}}\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"chargePointVendor\": \"ChargePoint\",\n    \"chargePointModel\": \"CP-2000\",\n    \"firmwareVersion\": \"2.5.1\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Registers the charging station with the CSMS.\n\nMust be called before StartTransaction — the system enforces this (returns 404 otherwise).\n\n**Expected response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"Accepted\",\n  \"currentTime\": \"...\",\n  \"interval\": 300\n}\n```"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Start Transaction",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('transactionId starts with TXN-', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.transactionId).to.match(/^TXN-/);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('idTagStatus is Accepted', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().idTagStatus).to.eql('Accepted');",
                  "});",
                  "// Auto-save transactionId to collection variable",
                  "const txnId = pm.response.json().transactionId;",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('transactionId', txnId);",
                  "console.log('transactionId saved:', txnId);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/ocpp/start-transaction", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","ocpp","start-transaction"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"stationId\": \"{{stationId}}\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:31:00Z\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"idTag\": \"USER-42\",\n    \"meterStart\": 0.0\n  }\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Starts a charging session.\n\nThe **transactionId** is automatically saved to the `transactionId` collection variable by the test script — subsequent requests use it automatically.\n\n**Expected response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"transactionId\": \"TXN-XXXXXXXX\",\n  \"idTagStatus\": \"Accepted\"\n}\n```"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "3. Meter Values",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Response status is Accepted', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('Accepted');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/ocpp/meter-values", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","ocpp","meter-values"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"stationId\": \"{{stationId}}\",\n  \"transactionId\": \"{{transactionId}}\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:35:00Z\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"energy\": 15.5,\n    \"power\": 7.2,\n    \"voltage\": 240,\n    \"current\": 30\n  }\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Sends periodic energy and power readings.\n\nThe `transactionId` is automatically populated from the collection variable set by Start Transaction.\n\nThis is also consumed by the Kafka `MeterValuesConsumer` which accumulates:\n- Total energy (kWh)\n- Average power (kW)\n- Charging duration (seconds)"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "3b. Meter Values (2nd reading)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/ocpp/meter-values", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","ocpp","meter-values"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"stationId\": \"{{stationId}}\",\n  \"transactionId\": \"{{transactionId}}\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:50:00Z\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"energy\": 32.1,\n    \"power\": 7.4,\n    \"voltage\": 239,\n    \"current\": 31\n  }\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "A second meter values reading to simulate ongoing charging. Run multiple times to see energy accumulation."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "4. Stop Transaction",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Response status is Accepted', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('Accepted');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/ocpp/stop-transaction", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","ocpp","stop-transaction"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"stationId\": \"{{stationId}}\",\n  \"transactionId\": \"{{transactionId}}\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T11:01:00Z\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"meterStop\": 45.2,\n    \"reason\": \"Local\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Ends the charging session.\n\nTotal energy consumed = `meterStop - meterStart` = 45.2 - 0.0 = **45.2 kWh**\n\nTransaction status changes from `ACTIVE` → `COMPLETED`."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Query API",
      "description": "Read-only endpoints to inspect station data, transactions, and energy reports",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get All Stations",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Response is an array', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Station EVSE-001 is registered', () => {",
                  "    const stations = pm.response.json();",
                  "    const found = stations.some(s => s.stationId === pm.collectionVariables.get('stationId'));",
                  "    pm.expect(found).to.be.true;",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/stations", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","stations"] },
            "description": "Returns all charging stations that have sent a BootNotification."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Active Transactions",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Response is an array', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/stations/transactions/active", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","stations","transactions","active"] },
            "description": "Returns all transactions with status=ACTIVE.\n\nRun this after Start Transaction (shows 1 result) and again after Stop Transaction (shows 0 results)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Charging History",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Response is an array', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});",
                  "if (pm.response.json().length > 0) {",
                  "    pm.test('First entry has transactionId', () => {",
                  "        pm.expect(pm.response.json()[0].transactionId).to.be.a('string');",
                  "    });",
                  "    pm.test('totalEnergyKwh is a number', () => {",
                  "        const energy = pm.response.json()[0].totalEnergyKwh;",
                  "        if (energy !== null) pm.expect(energy).to.be.a('number');",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/stations/{{stationId}}/history",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api","stations","{{stationId}}","history"]
            },
            "description": "Returns all transactions for the station, newest first.\n\nEach entry includes:\n- `transactionId`\n- `status` (ACTIVE / COMPLETED)\n- `startTime` / `stopTime`\n- `totalEnergyKwh` (meterStop - meterStart)\n- `durationSeconds`\n- `averagePowerKw` (from Kafka consumer)"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Energy Report (Last 24 Hours)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('totalEnergyKwh is a number', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().totalEnergyKwh).to.be.a('number');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('period is Last 24 hours', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().period).to.eql('Last 24 hours');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/stations/energy/last24hours", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","stations","energy","last24hours"] },
            "description": "Returns the total energy consumed across ALL stations in the last 24 hours.\n\n**Expected response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"totalEnergyKwh\": 45.2,\n  \"period\": \"Last 24 hours\"\n}\n```"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Error Cases",
      "description": "Verify error handling — these requests are expected to fail with 4xx responses",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Start Transaction — Unregistered Station (expect 404)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 404', () => pm.response.to.have.status(404));",
                  "pm.test('Error message mentions station', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('Station not registered');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/ocpp/start-transaction", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","ocpp","start-transaction"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"stationId\": \"EVSE-DOES-NOT-EXIST\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:31:00Z\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"idTag\": \"USER-42\",\n    \"meterStart\": 0.0\n  }\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Intentionally uses a stationId that hasn't sent a BootNotification.\n\nExpected: **404 Not Found** with message `Station not registered: EVSE-DOES-NOT-EXIST`"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Stop Transaction — Unknown Transaction (expect 404)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 404', () => pm.response.to.have.status(404));",
                  "pm.test('Error message mentions transaction', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('Transaction not found');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/ocpp/stop-transaction", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","ocpp","stop-transaction"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"stationId\": \"{{stationId}}\",\n  \"transactionId\": \"TXN-INVALID\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T11:01:00Z\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"meterStop\": 45.2,\n    \"reason\": \"Local\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Intentionally uses a fake transactionId.\n\nExpected: **404 Not Found** with message `Transaction not found: TXN-INVALID`"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Boot Notification — Missing stationId (expect 400)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 400', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
                  "pm.test('Validation error message present', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('Validation failed');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/ocpp/boot-notification", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","ocpp","boot-notification"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"chargePointVendor\": \"ChargePoint\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Missing the required `stationId` field.\n\nExpected: **400 Bad Request** with validation error message."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Second Station (Multi-Station Demo)",
      "description": "Demonstrates the system handling multiple stations simultaneously",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register Station 2",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/ocpp/boot-notification", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","ocpp","boot-notification"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"stationId\": \"EVSE-002\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"chargePointVendor\": \"ABB\",\n    \"chargePointModel\":  \"Terra-54\",\n    \"firmwareVersion\":   \"3.1.0\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Start Transaction on Station 2",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const txnId = pm.response.json().transactionId;",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('transactionId2', txnId);",
                  "console.log('Station 2 transactionId:', txnId);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/ocpp/start-transaction", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","ocpp","start-transaction"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"stationId\": \"EVSE-002\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:45:00Z\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"idTag\": \"USER-99\",\n    \"meterStart\": 0.0\n  }\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Active Transactions (should show 2)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/stations/transactions/active", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api","stations","transactions","active"] },
            "description": "After running both Start Transaction requests, this should return 2 active sessions."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
